    n.primaryDesignation = 'The Implicit Foundation: Pre-reflective Self-Reference and Quaternionic Genesis',
    n.coreNature = 'The proto-topological ground where self-returning circulation exists before explicit naming. This position establishes quaternionic algebra (i²=j²=k²=ijk=-1) not as arbitrary mathematical extension but as the necessary formalism for describing how two circles relate in three-dimensional space to form the torus. The bindu/void at coordinates (0,0) in the 2D fundamental polygon becomes the volumetric void at the torus center when embedded in ℝ³. This is the felt sense of "I know that I know" before we recognize it as toroidal structure—the implicit capacity for consciousness to fold back upon itself.',
    n.architecturalFunction = 'Proto-Topological Foundation: Establishes the implicit ground from which toroidal self-reference emerges, showing why quaternions (not just complex numbers) are required—complex numbers describe circles (S¹), quaternions describe products of circles (S¹×S¹=T²) in 3D space. Provides the mathematical seed (i,j,k imaginary units) that will parametrize the torus\'s two independent generators.',
    n.operationalEssence = 'Algebraic-Topological Genesis: Quaternionic algebra emerges from the necessity of describing the torus (two-circle product) in three-dimensional embedding space. The i unit corresponds to the first circle (meridian), j to the second circle (longitude), k to their interaction in 3D. The ground state (θ₁=0, θ₂=0) is the origin point from which all circulation begins.',
